defaultge. E3G works closely with like-minded partners in government, politics, civil society, science, the media, public interest foundations and elsewhere. Further information is available at 
defaultwww.e3g.org
default .
default2.2
default              
defaultE3G welcomes the
default ECC committee inquiry into CCS. E3G has been closely involved in UK, European and International efforts to accelerate action on CCS over the past decade, including the creation of the EU’s NER300 funding mechanism and the Near Zero Emission Coal (NZEC) pr
defaultoject between the UK, EU and China.
default E3G is represented on the Advisory Council of the European Technology Platform for Zero 
defaultEmission Fossil Fuel Power Plants (ZEP) and is a member of the International Environmental NGO network on CCS.
default2.3
default              
defaultE3G recognises th
defaultat it will be 
defaultdifficult for 
defaultthe international community to secure a global deal on climate unless key countries and constituencies 
defaultfeel
default that they can maintain energy security while reducing emissions. In our view, the deployment of CCS is therefore both a 
defaulttechnological necessity (as a stable climate will only be secured if we limit the 
defaultstock
default of CO2 emissions in the atmosphere) and a political intervention that can shape the space for other actions and agreements.
